div.div:
It's a common misconception that you'll see massive benefits from switching to anything Rust based, especially if you are on of those that aren't going to develop your backend in RUst. Since Tauri uses Rust in the backend it does have benefits, but the webview itself isn't made in Rust and you're not going to experience a massive performance boost over something like Electron when it comes to the actual frontend.
It's better to choose something that fits into your overall tech stack than to pick something just because you can.

div.div:
It's a common misconception that you'll see massive benefits from switching to anything Rust based, especially if you are on of those that aren't going to develop your backend in RUst. Since Tauri uses Rust in the backend it does have benefits, but the webview itself isn't made in Rust and you're not going to experience a massive performance boost over something like Electron when it comes to the actual frontend.
It's better to choose something that fits into your overall tech stack than to pick something just because you can.
